If you don't own an Blu-Ray burner, you can easily and very quick convert 
individual .m2ts clips (in folder BDMV-STREAM) without re-encoding to .mkv with MKVToolnix.
MKVToolnix is free software - http://www.videohelp.com/tools/MKVtoolnix
Those .mkv files are then playable from external HDD in all Blu-Ray and multimedia players 
and even on most newer TV's with DTS support (Samsung, LG &amp; Panasonic TV's - models from 2012 and up and Sony's from 2013 and up)



